        "timestamp": "2018-11-02 12:59:29.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2\n\nThe intent was that identifiers in DG should follow more or less the same rules as identifiers in Java, where colon is not supported as part of a variable name.  If we change the rules and allow colon to be part of an identifier, then we take away the option of using colon as an operator - for example, if we wanted to add the trinary operator ( condition ? true : false).",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
